  "prompt": "How can I know that I am not in the friend zone?",
  "response": "Here are some signs you're not in the friend zone:\n\n1. Clear signs of romantic interest\n- They often initiate contact\n- They make time for you specifically\n- They compliment you frequently\n- They show physical affection or flirting\n- They get jealous when you talk about other potential partners\n\n2. Body language indicators\n- Prolonged eye contact\n- Standing/sitting close to you\n- Touching you casually\n- Facing towards you during conversations\n\n3. Communication patterns\n- They share personal details and emotions\n- They seek your opinion and value your perspective\n- They want to spend one-on-one time together\n- They make future plans that include you\n\n4. Direct indicators\n- They've expressed romantic interest\n- They've asked you on a date\n- They've suggested being more than friends\n- They've outright told you they like you\n\n5. What to avoid\n- Always being the listener\n- Never receiving romantic attention\n- Only meeting in group settings\n- Being treated strictly platonically\n\nRemember, clear communication is key. If you're unsure, it's best to have an honest conversation about your feelings and intentions.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
